> Never roasted fruit before? Now's your chance to discover the beauty of natural sugars melting into deliciousness. Here, we roast apple with a colorful root veggie jumble, adding savory-sweetness to a meal with rich flavors. A creamy mustard sauce is drizzled over perfectly cooked pork filet for a decadent finish. We won't judge if you can't help yourself from licking the plate when it's all over.

== Roasted Veggies and Pork ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Russet Potato{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Strip @Rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4). Halve, core, and cut @Apple{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes, carrots, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, chopped rosemary, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (Divide between 2 baking sheets for 4 servings; roast on top and middle racks.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the pork and apple then).

While veggies roast, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Rub with a drizzle of oil.

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, add pork to same baking sheet. Carefully toss apple with veggies. (For 4 servings, add pork to one sheet and apple to other.)

Return to top rack until veggies and apple are browned and tender and pork is cooked through, ~{18-22%minutes} more. (For 4, return sheet with pork and veggies to top rack and sheet with veggies and apple to middle rack.)

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork; Once veggies have roasted for ~{12%minutes}, add chicken or beef to sheet. Roast until chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}, or until beef reaches to desired doneness, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Creamy Mustard Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Honey{2%teaspoon}, and @Dijon Mustard{4%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Once pork is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{}. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice crosswise.

> Love extra-crispy veggies? While pork rests, heat broiler to high and return veggies to oven for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

Divide pork and roasted veggies and apple between plates. Serve with creamy mustard on the side for dipping.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.